                  IMPERIUM TERRANUM 2 - War of the Worlds
                  ---------------------------------------


IMPERIUM TERRANUM is a complex world-simulation. It is your objective to 
enlarge your civilisation in the technological and economical way and to
settle them in space. The great aim is the implementation of the 
NEW-LIFEFORM-project. This enables the transition to a new lifeform,
that base on pure energy, independent of time and space, perfect and immortal.

It would be no problem to manage this, if there wouldn't be the (normal)
adversities of live: strange civilisations, which want to reach the same 
goal as first, and so want to knock you out, deceitful civilisations, which
want the absolute control in the quandrant, evil civilisations, which want 
to snuff out your life, thievish neighbours, which will steal your credits, 
military, which want to gain control with a putsch, very bad and terrible 
disasters.


Version 2 of IMPERIUM TERRANUM has following improvements:

   - up to 5 human player can fight against
   
   - forming of powerfull ship-fleets

   - planets can be automatical irrigated by ships

   - much more options at negotiations, and now also at development aid

   - many new functions were inserted
        - steady wormholes with constant start- and endpoints
        - searching for ships
        - the possibility, to spy, on which planet the enemy has installed
          his capital-projects
        - increase of the difficulty-level within the game
        - ...

   - new difficulties and complications e.g.
        - the Ja´Hadr
        - the Maques
        - military-putsch and following split of your empire and civil war
        - ...

   - stunning THX®-like Dolby-Surround®-sounds with damned good bass
     as well as a proper intro

   ... and of course bugfixes

Unfortunately there is a big disadvantage: Because of the many improvements
against IT1 all disks have to be new @{"bought/provided/organized" LINK Order_eng},
because the mass of the new and changed files would have required more than
three Update-Disks. This would've failed my price-calculations.
Of course the, now, six disks are still free for copy and can be downloaded
very reasonable from mailboxes, Aminet or @{"VWP-Homepage" LINK Homepage}.
Registred users can take the keyfile of the old version, without to register
again.
Another huge disadvantage is the fact, that the game is complete german
(perhaps changing very soon).



@ENDNODE
@NODE STAR_TREK_eng


             IMPERIUM TERRANUM 2 - A Tribute To STAR TREK
                         - Special Edition -
             --------------------------------------------

This Special Edition is accordant to the "normal" version of @{"IT2" LINK War_of_the_Worlds_eng}
in wide parts. Only that here  - as my personal tribute to this legend - all
civilisations, symbols as well as many sounds, ships, technologies and much
more are the same as in the STAR-TREK-universe.

The STAR-TREK-Edition is a unique version, that is not developed any further.
But it's possible, to copy it in the directory of IT2 - War Of The Worlds,
and to save, because of a few same files, harddisk-space.
The normal version and the Special Edition are able to run with the same
keyfile, so there is no need for a new registration.

IT2 - A Tribute To STAR TREK requires a harddisk to run.


