     T h e   W a v e T r a c e r   D S   s o f t w a r e p a c k a g e
     -----------------------------------------------------------------


The WaveTracer DS softwarepackage actually contains following mainprogramms:

   - WaveTracer DS - universal utility for soundediting
   - CineTracer - converts raytracing-scenes into the CineData-format,
                  that can be transformed to audio-datas by the WaveTracer
   - AnimFX - special Anim-player for the formats CDXL and
              IFF-ANIM 5, 7 and 8, supports animations with sound 
              (these anims can be created with the CineTracer and WaveTracer)



                     WaveTracer DS  Mark IV
                     ----------------------

Originally designed to produce synthetic sounds, the WaveTracer DS has been
developed to a powerfull soundtool. You can - beside the pure soundsyntese - 
edit, process and convert samples to different soundformats with this 
programm.
Every normal and Dolby-Surround®-Sound, that can be heard in
@{"IMPERIUM TERRANUM 2" LINK War_Of_The_Worlds_eng} , was generated or processed with the WaveTracer DS. 
For a short overview, now are listed a few features of WaveTracer DS Mark IV 
- the latest version - :

   - create and edit sounds
   - converting of different soundformats (8SVX, 16SV, 16SX, 24SX, ANIM,
     AIFF, HSN, RIFF-WAVE, SONIX®.instr, MAUD, VOICE, CineData etc.)
   - voluminous soundeffects (everything you can else do on electronical
     way like Accords, Chorus, Dynamic-Compressor, Egalizer, 
     Fast-/Surround-Echo, Filter, Technoise, Tone and many more)
   - real modular structure for effective Plug-Ins with additional external 
     Load-, Save- or Effectmodules (Playmodules for various soundcards
     are in preparation)
   - Dolby-Surround®-Coding of sounds
   - play-back of up to 6 Channels with Dolby-Surround®-coding
   - sounds are played on standard-AMIGAS® without soundcard in 16 Bit
   - special Dolby-Surround® effectmodules for spatial tones
     (Dolby® De- and Encoder, 3D-Surround etc.)
   - many soundmodes available (Mono, Stereo, StereoPlus®, 3Channel, DTS-Quadro,
     Dolby-Surround®, AC-3®, DTS®)
   - soundprocessing in broadcast-quality (24 up to maximum 32 Bit)
   - soundoutput in 8, 16 or 24 Bit
   - different kinds of Sample-Compression
   - Playlist with many manipulation-possibilities

And what contrast the WaveTracer DS especially with the competition:
   - The SpectraFX®-Algorithm: spatial sound with a quite normal 
     stereo-system
   - creating of animations with sound in (backward-)compatible
     IFF-ANIM-Formats
   - far-reaching include of Anim-picture-datas, for a simple and
     effective injection of sound into this animation
   - support of an Audio-Alphachannel
   - Copyright-Information can be hidden in samples (not as Chunk, but
     really direct in the sample; this method, named Hidden-Crypto® was
     developed by VIRTUAL WORLDS® and can't be found anywere else!)
   - wide-range, licence-free information for programmers both about the
     used sound- and dataformats with it's compression-methods and
     for the programming of new Load-, Save- or Effectmodules

Programm and documentation are complete in german. But direct in the programm
further languages can be initialised by a special localisation (english is 
included, translations into other speeches are also possible).

Requires AA-Chipset and OS 3.0. Available in version Mark IV e.g. direct
from @{"Producer" LINK Order_eng}



                           CineTracer Mark I
                           -----------------


The CineTracer is part of the WaveTracer-softwarepackage and represents a
converter, that enables it, to separate the information out of the datafiles
of various raytracers, that are needed, to generate a perfect, stunning 
Dolby-Surround®-Sound for a raytracing-animation. These scene-datas can be
stored in the CineData-format. You only have to specify, which objects of the
scene should be sounded with which sample in which volume - the rest will be 
done (with really breathtaking results) - by the WaveTracer!

With help of the CineData-Loadmodule and various (in the package contained)
tools, the WaveTracer can subsequently generate a sound , that fits, without
time-consuming editing or programming, perfect to the rendered animation.

This generated sample can be integrated by the WaveTracer DS and the
AnimInjector-Savemodule into the animationen. Then it can be played by
the @{"AnimFX-Player" LINK AnimFX_eng}, that is included in the package.


@ENDNODE
@NODE AnimFX_eng


                 AnimFX- and BigAnimFX-Animationplayer
                 --------------------------------------


AnimFX is an animationplayer, that can play animations with sound, like these
that are made with the WaveTracer-Savemodule AnimInjector. The common formats
IFF-ANIM 5, 7 and 8 are supported. As a little extra-feature, AnimFX also
supports the CDXL-format (I didn't found a player for this format yet).
BigAnimFX is, beside the mentioned features, additional able, to play anims, 
that are larger, than the useable memory.

The AnimFX-package contains also an IFF-Demo-animation, that shows, how 
Sound-ANIMs can look and listen!

Furthermore belongs to the package a complete documentation about all actual
ANIM-Formats, which was put together by the original single-documentations of 
the developers (documentation about AnimBrushes are not included). The 
ANIM-Formats 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7 and 8 as well as the format of ANIMs with Sound
are described in detail.

Attention: The WaveTracer DS softwarepackage contains the program AnimFX only
           with a short-documentation!


@ENDNODE
@NODE Order_eng


You can get VIRTUAL WORLDS productes either on various PD-series or direct 
from the the producer. Or download the Shareware-versions from our new
                           @{" Homepage " LINK Homepage}.

To get the keyfile, please fill out the registerform. Print it and send it 
with by mail to the adress at the end of the form. Or you attach it to an
e-mail and send it to the e-mail-adress, also at the end of the form.

There are two ways to pay the charge:

TRANSFER your MONEY to the account listed in the registerform. 
As payment-reason or purpose please fill in street and town with postcode
COMPLETELY (!!!) (your NAME will already apear in the control-bill of our
bank)! 
When you order by mail, please include the printed registerform
AND a copy of your transfer-receipt.
When you order by e-mail, please fill in the same name and adress as in the
attached registerform, so we can't do mistakes at your costs.

We also take CASH and Eurocheques, which is send by mail together with the 
registerform. But it's your risk, if something failes at the mail-way.

The delivery can take up to max. four weeks (mail-way, checking the transfer-
information).

Attention
---------

Ordering by e-mail:
You will get your keyfile, when ordered a registred version, by an e-mail 
from us. The disks will arrive later on the standard mail-way.  
Actually you only can pay for an e-mail-order with a money-transfer.


And now the charges for the different products. The single prices are for 
Germany (in DM), the prices in brackets are for Europe (in DM) and for the
rest of the world (in US$):

